<subSubSection id="03A7EE93FF85FFFA3DEFB4545FE8C78D" pageId="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4B02BD18FF85FFFA3DEFB4545FE8C78D" blockId="7.[151,1436,1764,2005]" pageId="7">
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3DEFB4545C5FC730" bold="true" box="[199,321,1871,1896]" pageId="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8CBDC69BFF85FFFA3C63B44B5CEDC730" box="[331,499,1872,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mertliki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3C63B44B5CEDC730" box="[331,499,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="7">Drilus mertliki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3CD5B4545F44C730" bold="true" box="[509,602,1871,1896]" pageId="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62FADC71FF85FFFA3CD5B4545F44C730" box="[509,602,1871,1896]" pageId="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8CBDC69BFF85FFFA3FD0B44A5EB2C730" box="[760,940,1872,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanliurfensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3FD0B44A5E12C730" box="[760,780,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="7">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3E35B44B5EB2C730" box="[797,940,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="7">sanliurfensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3E9EB454590DC730" bold="true" box="[950,1043,1871,1896]" pageId="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62FADC71FF85FFFA3E9EB454590DC730" box="[950,1043,1871,1896]" pageId="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but differs from the latter by the pronotum with convex lateral margins and prominent hind angles (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF85FFFA3EA7B46F590CC7D4" box="[911,1042,1908,1933]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1423,1446]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,204,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1403]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 21. Pronota of Drilus species. 13, Drilus badius sp. nov.; 14, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 15, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 16, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 17, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 18, D. robustus sp. nov.; 19, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 20, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 21, D. turcicus sp. nov. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232881/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Figs 16, 19</figureCitation>
), and the narrower paramera (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF85FFFA3842B46F5DFFC7E8" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 45" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1845,1868]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,529,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,517,1825]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 45. Male genitalia of Drilus species. 34, Drilus badius sp. nov.; 35, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 36, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 37, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 38, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 39, D. rectus Schaufuss, 1867 (Turkey, Adana Prov.); 40, D. robustus sp. nov.; 41, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 42, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 43, D. turcicus sp. nov.; 44, D. iranicus Wittmer, 1967; 45, Drilus sp. (Abkhazia). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232883/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Figs 37, 41</figureCitation>
). The similarly-colored 
<taxonomicName id="8CBDC69BFF85FFFA3CDCB4835F25C7E8" box="[500,571,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3CDCB4835F25C7E8" box="[500,571,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="7">Drilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. from Caucasus differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8CBDC69BFF85FFFA3E85B4825939C7E8" box="[941,1063,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mertliki" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3E85B4825EDFC7E8" box="[941,961,1945,1968]" italics="true" pageId="7">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3EF8B4835939C7E8" box="[976,1063,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="7">mertliki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF85FFFA3918B4835995C7E9" bold="true" box="[1072,1163,1944,1969]" pageId="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="62FADC71FF85FFFA3918B4835995C7E9" box="[1072,1163,1944,1969]" pageId="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the relatively shorter phallus and differently shaped paramera (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF85FFFA3F4FB4A75FF7C78D" box="[615,745,1980,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 45" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1845,1868]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,529,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,517,1825]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 45. Male genitalia of Drilus species. 34, Drilus badius sp. nov.; 35, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 36, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 37, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 38, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 39, D. rectus Schaufuss, 1867 (Turkey, Adana Prov.); 40, D. robustus sp. nov.; 41, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 42, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 43, D. turcicus sp. nov.; 44, D. iranicus Wittmer, 1967; 45, Drilus sp. (Abkhazia). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232883/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Figs 37, 45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="03A7EE93FF8AFFF53DEFB38C5F52C3FC" pageId="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="4B02BD18FF8AFFF53DEFB38C599AC360" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1112]" pageId="8">
<emphasis id="79C9610AFF8AFFF53DEFB38C5C47C0E8" bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="8">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus id="940603BAFF8AFFF53C86B38C5F08C0E8" box="[430,534,151,176]" pageId="8">holotype</typeStatus>
). Body 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53F5BB3835F88C0E8" box="[627,662,152,176]" pageId="8" value="3.2">3.2</number>
times longer than width at humeri, dark brown to black, antennae brown, scape, pedicel, legs and last abdominal ventrite yellowish brown; body covered with yellow pubescence (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF8AFFF53DB7B3C45DF8C0A0" box="[159,230,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1396,203,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[172,1408,195,1856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Habitus images of Drilus species. 1, Drilus akbesianus (Fairmaire, 1895); 2, D. badius sp. nov.; 3, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 4, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 5, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 6, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 7, D. rectus Schaufuss, 1867; 8, D. robustus sp. nov.; 9, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 10, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 11, D. turcicus sp. nov.; 12, D. iranicus Wittmer, 1967. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232880/files/figure.png" pageId="8">
Fig. 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53DFEB3C45DF8C0A0" box="[214,230,223,248]" pageId="8" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head including eyes about as wide as anterior margin of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF8AFFF53932B3C45971C0A0" box="[1050,1135,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1423,1446]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,204,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1403]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 21. Pronota of Drilus species. 13, Drilus badius sp. nov.; 14, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 15, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 16, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 17, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 18, D. robustus sp. nov.; 19, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 20, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 21, D. turcicus sp. nov. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232881/files/figure.png" pageId="8">
Fig. 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53979B3C45971C0A0" box="[1105,1135,223,248]" pageId="8" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
), with shallow depression medially, lateral margins above antennal sockets slightly elevated, sparsely punctured, with sparse semierect pubescence; clypeal margin widely concave. Eyes medium-sized, their frontal distance 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF539A6B23359AFC118" box="[1166,1201,296,320]" pageId="8" value="1.8">1.8</number>
times eye diameter. Mandibles curved, shiny, incisor margin with conspicuous tooth in middle part. Labrum transverse; maxillary palpi slender, ultimate palpomere apically slightly flattened, obliquely cut. Antennae pectinate, reaching one third of elytral length, antennomere 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53CFCB28F5CFCC1F4" box="[468,482,404,428]" pageId="8" value="3.0">3</number>
serrate, antennomeres 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53FCFB28F5E3EC1F4" box="[743,800,404,428]" pageId="8" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4–10</number>
pectinate, apical antennomere simple, longest (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF8AFFF53813B28F5891C1F5" box="[1339,1423,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 33" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1794,1817]" captionTargetBox="[155,1414,201,1764]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1773]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 33. Antennae of Drilus species. 22, Drilus badius sp. nov.; 23, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 24, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 25, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 26, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 27, D. rectus Schaufuss, 1867; 28, D. robustus sp. nov.; 29, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 30, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 31, D. turcicus sp. nov. Drilus robustus sp. nov., male. 32, leg; 33, last abdominal segments. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232882/files/figure.png" pageId="8">
Fig. 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53858B28F5891C1F5" box="[1392,1423,404,429]" pageId="8" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum slightly convex, transverse, widest at hind agles, 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53E78B2A35E6DC188" box="[848,883,440,464]" pageId="8" value="1.7">1.7</number>
times wider posteriorly than length at midline. Anterior margin almost straight, lateral margins sinuate, posterior margin slightly convex. Anterior angles inconspicuous; posterior angles prominent, acute, slightly turned upward (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF8AFFF53EF9B2E4593AC240" box="[977,1060,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1423,1446]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,204,1401]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1403]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 21. Pronota of Drilus species. 13, Drilus badius sp. nov.; 14, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 15, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 16, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 17, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 18, D. robustus sp. nov.; 19, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 20, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 21, D. turcicus sp. nov. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232881/files/figure.png" pageId="8">
Fig. 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF5392DB2E4593AC240" box="[1029,1060,511,536]" pageId="8" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
); surface of disc sparsely covered with fine punctures, with sparse semierect setae. Scutellum flat, gradually narrowed, sparsely punctured; apex rounded. Prosternum transverse, slightly wrinkled, frontal margin almost straight, prosternal process minute, steeply declivitous. Mesoventrite widely v-shaped, anteromedially depressed. Elytra subparallel-sided, wrinkled, sparsely and finely punctured, covered with sparse semierect long pubescence, denser apically. Legs slender, slightly compressed, with sparse, long, semierect setae, tarsomeres 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53EBAB1AF5EA2C294" box="[914,956,692,716]" pageId="8" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
gradually shortened, tarsomere 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53800B1AF5828C294" box="[1320,1334,692,716]" pageId="8" value="4.0">4</number>
shortest, apical tarsomere slender, about as long as antennomere 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53E3EB1C35E3AC2A8" box="[790,804,728,752]" pageId="8" value="1.0">1</number>
, slightly longer than combined lengths of tarsomeres 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF538A6B1C35882C2A8" box="[1422,1436,728,752]" pageId="8" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53DE2B1E75DC5C34C" box="[202,219,764,788]" pageId="8" value="4.0">4</number>
. Aedeagus with robust, considerably curved phallus; paramera long, slender, covered with setae, mainly ventrally; phallobase long, v-shaped (
<figureCitation id="D386A19DFF8AFFF53F14B0045F8EC360" box="[572,656,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 45" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1845,1868]" captionTargetBox="[163,1430,529,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,517,1825]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 45. Male genitalia of Drilus species. 34, Drilus badius sp. nov.; 35, D. huijbregtsi sp. nov.; 36, D. latithorax Pic, 1902; 37, D. mertliki sp. nov.; 38, D. obscuricornis Pic, 1899; 39, D. rectus Schaufuss, 1867 (Turkey, Adana Prov.); 40, D. robustus sp. nov.; 41, D. sanliurfensis sp. nov.; 42, D. teunisseni sp. nov.; 43, D. turcicus sp. nov.; 44, D. iranicus Wittmer, 1967; 45, Drilus sp. (Abkhazia). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232883/files/figure.png" pageId="8">
Fig. 
<number id="FD75AF3FFF8AFFF53F58B03B5F8EC360" box="[624,656,800,824]" pageId="8" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
). Female and immature stages are unknown.
</paragraph>
